This paper deals with communication protocols in ad-hoc radio networks, which is a topic related to networked systems and communication (cs.NI). The paper also involves the analysis of the complexity of the protocol, which is a common theme in distributed computing (cs.DC) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of polynomially large labels suggests that information theory (cs.IT) may also be relevant. Finally, the paper mentions an open problem related to efficient gossiping, which is a topic in distributed algorithms and protocols (cs.SI).
